                <h2 style="color:#000; font-weight: bold">How It Works</h2>
                <img src="/images/how_it_works.png" alt="" style="width:100%;">
            </div>
            <hr>
            <div>
                <h2 style="color:#000; font-weight: bold">How to Use</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li style="line-height: 25px;"> - Buyer sends offer</li>
                    <li style="line-height: 25px;"> - Producer accepts offer</li>
                    <li style="line-height: 25px;"> - Buyer pays Ant Commodity</li>
                    <li style="line-height: 25px;"> - Ant Commodity inspects shipment</li>
                    <li style="line-height: 25px;"> - Producer receives payment</li>
                    <li style="line-height: 25px;"> - Buyer receives shipment</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <hr>
            <div>
                <h2 style="color:#000; font-weight: bold">Part 01: Buyer searches for commodity</h2>
                <p>
                    Buyer view commodity listings posted by producers by searching on the Ant Commodity website.
                    Buyer can contact Ant Commodity Field Officers for support via FindCorrectCommodity@AntCommodity.com.
                    <br><br>
                    Buyer can learn more information about the producer by going onto producer’s profile page.
                    On the profile page, buyer has access to the inspection report, pictures and other information
                    of the producer’s business operation took by Ant Commodity.
                </p>
            </div>
            <hr>
            <div>
                <h2 style="color: #000; font-weight: bold">Part 02: Buyer requests for more information, samples, testing etc.  [Optional]</h2>
                <p>
                    Buyer sends message to producer to get clarification on the listed commodity or ask for samples and testing’s.
                    Depend on the request, buyer may be asked to send a payment to cover the cost of the activity.
                    For samples and testing, Ant Commodity will carry out the work independently.
                    <br><br>
                    All requests and messages sent by the buyer are first reviewed by a field officer at Ant Commodity.
                    Ant Commodity field officer communicates with the producer and reply to the buyer accordingly.
                    Typical reply time is around 4-5 hours but vary in non-working hours and holidays.
                </p>
            </div>
            <hr>
            <div>
                <h2 style="color: #000; font-weight: bold">Part 03: Buyer sends offer, and starts negotiating</h2>
                <p>
                    Buyer starts the negotiation with the producer by sending the first offer. To submit an
                    offer successfully buyer is required to submit offer price in FOB–USD currency,
                    quantity buyer want to purchase, port of delivery, incoterms and medium. If buyer
                    has additional requests like lab testing, specific packing method, insurance etc.,
                    buyer should mention that in the notes section.
                    <br><br>
                    Ant Commodity first receives the offer, and communicate with the producer. After
                    consultation with the producer,Ant Commodity reply to the buyer with a formal
                    acceptance or counter offer. Ant Commodity does not provide any advice or influence on
                    the decision-making process to the producer nor buyer.
                </p>
            </div>
            <hr>
            <div>
                <h2 style="color: #000; font-weight: bold">Part 04: Buyer sends payment to Ant Commodity</h2>
                <p>
                    After buyer and producer accept on the price, Ant Commodity creates a contract based on
                    the agreed terms and send payment instructions to buyer. Buyer is required to send the payment
                    during the mentioned time frame.
                    <br><br>
                    Ant Commodity does not distribute the money to the producer until Ant Commodity
                    inspects the shipment and arrange delivery to the buyer.
                </p>
            </div>
            <hr>
            <div>
                <h2 style="color: #000; font-weight: bold">Part 05: Ant Commodityinspects shipment, ship to buyer</h2>
                <p>
                    Ant Commodity inspects the shipment to see whether the shipment is prepared according to the agreed terms.
                    If buyer has requested additional testing, Ant Commodity will perform it at this stage.
                    After receiving the inspector’s approval, Ant Commodity will release the
                    payment to producer after deducting the Ant Commodity ’s commission and other expenses.
                    <br><br>
                    Any discrepancies of the shipment will be communicated with the buyer and producer.
                </p>
            </div>
